   "source": [
    "# In-Vehicle Coupon Recommendation Classification Project"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eb703186",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Objective\n",
    "\n",
    "The primary goal of this project is to build a predictive machine learning model that classifies whether a vehicle occupant will accept a given coupon or not. The data simulates various real-world driving and personal scenarios including weather conditions, destination, companions, and user demographics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5d38bdea",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Business Relevance\n",
    "\n",
    "A higher coupon acceptance rate directly impacts advertising effectiveness and consumer engagement. By accurately predicting coupon acceptance, advertisers and in-vehicle recommendation systems can:\n",
    "\n",
    "Increase customer conversion and revenue by targeting users more effectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "Optimize promotional budgets by identifying promising contexts and user profiles.\n",
    "\n",
    "Personalize offers in real-time for maximum impact."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ff80b9e3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Scope of the Model\n",
    "\n",
    "The classification model will be built to distinguish between users who will and will not accept coupons based on contextual and demographic factors. This will form the backbone of a smarter, data-driven coupon delivery system."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "id": "b9fcef2a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
